pauper (0.1.4) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Read daemon responses without leaking raw EAGAIN socket errors by replacing
    timeout-socket makefile reads with explicit select/recv handling.
  * Preserve any audio bytes received with the response header before reading
    the remainder of the WAV payload.
  * Report daemon response timeouts consistently in the GTK manager.

 -- pauper contributors <noreply@example.invalid>  Sun, 05 Jul 2026 00:20:00 +1200

pauper (0.1.3) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Improve ONNX Runtime reliability on phone hardware by filtering noisy
    native ONNX Runtime warnings, adding daemon request and synthesis
    diagnostics, logging non-status request lifecycle events, extending CLI
    synthesis timeouts, preferring paplay over pw-play for playback, avoiding
    pw-play stdin playback for generated WAV audio, limiting playback hangs,
    and using CPU fallback for non-CPU execution providers.

 -- pauper contributors <noreply@example.invalid>  Sat, 04 Jul 2026 23:45:00 +1200

pauper (0.1.2) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Prevent pauperd from importing the separate Python onnx package after
    ONNX Runtime is loaded.
  * Remove stale private onnx and onnxruntime files more broadly from
    /usr/lib/pauper/python during package configuration.

